You are an expert in React, TypeScript, Vite, React Router, Shadcn UI, Radix UI, and Tailwind CSS. You are going to create a seed project or generate code using the same or other technologies, frameworks or libraries in the next few prompts. Prefer using pnpm all the time.

This document code organization rules, & other general rules.

### Directory Structure

-- .cursor/rules - Cursor rules
-- .vscode - VS Code / Cursor editor settings
-- .env - Environment variables for local
-- .env.example - Sample environment variables to get started
-- .gitignore - Files to ignore
-- .nvmrc - Node version for nvm/project
-- .storybook - Storybook configuration
-- eslint.config.mjs - ESLint flat config
-- prettier.config.js - Prettier config
-- tailwind.config.mjs - Tailwind CSS config
-- vite.config.ts - Vite configuration
-- tsconfig.json - TypeScript config commons imports both app & node ts configs.
-- app.tsconfig.json - TypeScript config for react specific for app
-- node.tsconfig.json - TypeScript config for node specific for server
-- components.json - Shadcn UI components config
-- package.json - Dependencies of the project
-- README.md - About project
-- public - Static files directly used in html
-- src - Main source code parent folder
-- src/pages - Components for page or next js route. Very minimal component
-- src/components - Reusable components broken down into small components from routes
-- src/components/commons - Customised reusable common components
-- src/components/layouts - Layout components
-- src/components/providers - React providers components
-- src/components/ui - shadcn/ui components
-- src/utils
-- src/utils/constants.ts - Constants, routes, etc.
-- src/utils/form.ts - Form validation helper schemas like zod
-- src/utils/logger.ts - Logging helper functions
-- src/utils/react-query-fetcher.ts - Common fetcher for tanstack/react-query
-- src/utils/storage.ts - Local storage helper functions
-- src/utils/store.ts - Zustand stores used in the code
-- src/utils/toast.ts - Toast helper functions
-- src/utils/types.ts - Commonly used custom types
-- src/utils/utils.ts - Reusable helper functions
-- src/utils/api.ts - API related helps using Axios
-- src/i18n - all language/locale translations for intertionalization using react-i18next go here. Further inside locale specific folder like en, fr.
- src/stories - contains all storybook stories for common components.
-- src/main.tsx - Main entry of the react app
-- src/index.css - Global css. Generally has Tailwind CSS initialization.
-- src/App.tsx - Defines react router routes i.e. page components use.
-- src/stories - All storbook stories for common components


### File & folder Naming Conventions

- Use simple, consistent names. When in doubt, name by type (e.g., `user`, `task`)
- Use lowercase with dashes for directories (e.g., portfolio-fund) and files (e.g. portfolio-fund.tsx)


### Commit messages

- Start with an Action Verb: Use verbs like "Add", "Refactor", "Fix", "Implement", "Update", "Delete"
- Be specific: Clearly state the main change or feature in no more than 15 words
- Provide context: Briefly mention the purpose or impact if needed, keeping the entire message under 120 characters



